First, let's compute the matrix \emph{B}

\begin{align*}
B &= A^2 + 3A + 2I \\
&= \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
-6 & 8 \\
-4 & 6
\end{array}\right]\left[ \begin{array}{cc}
-6 & 8 \\
-4 & 6
\end{array}\right] + 3 \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
-6 & 8 \\
-4 & 6
\end{array}\right] + 2 \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
1 & 0 \\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right] \\
&= \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
4 & 0 \\
0 & 4
\end{array}\right] + \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
-18 & 24 \\
-12 & 18
\end{array}\right] + \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
2 & 0 \\
0 & 2
\end{array}\right] \\
&= \left[ \begin{array}{cc}
-12 & 24 \\
-12 & 24
\end{array}\right]\end{align*}

And clearly this matrix has determinant zero.
